value.value: A xylem fiber cell (PO:0000274) with bordered pits with pit cavities.

definition.value: Fiber tracheids generally have pointed ends and bordered pits that have lenticular to slit-like apertures. If both libriform fiber cells (PO:0004520) and fiber tracheids are present, the libriform fiber cells usually have thicker walls. Fiber tracheids have bordered pits with smaller pit cavities than the vessel members (PO:0002003) or tracheids (PO:0000301) of the same wood and a distinct pit cavity leading to the cell lumen through the cell wall.

value.value: A portion of primary xylem (PO:0005849) tissue that has as part one or more metaxylem tracheary elements (PO:0025576) embedded in parenchyma (PO:0005421) tissue and may contain xylem fiber cells (PO:0000274).

definition.value: Metaxylem has larger tracheary elements (PO:0000290) than the protoxylem (PO:0000272), and develops after the formation of the protoxylem, once elongation of the plant axis (PO:0025004) has completed.

value.value: A cambial initial cell (PO:0000295) which is destined to differentiate into secondary phloem.

definition.value: Phloem islands can be formed in the middle of the xylem.

value.value: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) which is a whole plant (PO:0000003) in the plant zygote stage (PO:0001097).

definition.value: A plant zygote is a whole plant that is a single cell formed by fertilization (syngamy).

value.value: A sporocyte (PO:0006204) that produces four haploid (1n) megaspores (PO:0020019).

definition.value: If you are annotating to this structure for Zea mays or other grasses, please also add an annotation to the corresponding floret type. Choose the most specific term possible from: spikelet floret (PO:0009082), ear floret (PO:0006354), upper floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear (PO:0006350), upper floret of sessile spikelet of ear (PO:0006352).

value.value: A multi-tissue plant structure development stage (PO:0025571) that has as primary participant a single fruit (PO:0009001).

definition.value: Defined by characteristic morphological, structural, histological or other visible features of a fruit. Includes as subclasses fruit formation stage (PO:0025501) and fruit ripening stage (PO:0025502). May have as part a seed development stage (PO:0001170). This stage applies to an individual fruit. For development stages of a whole plant (PO:0000003) based on fruit development, use whole plant fruit development stage (PO:0025500) or its subclasses.

value.value: A vascular leaf initiation stage (PO:0007040) during which the vascular leaf founder cells (PO:0025592) of the shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148) form a vascular leaf anlagen (PO:0025431).

definition.value: The initial stage of leaf development when cells in the shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148) are already determined to form a vascular leaf primordium (PO:0000017), but the primordium is not yet morphologically distinguishable.

value.value: Stages of development of the anther defined by characteristic morphological, cytological, histological or other visible features.
An initial stage during which archesporial cells arise in four corners of L2 layer. Change in shape of primordia to more oval.
Stage during which the microsporocytes become conspicuous.
A microgametophyte development stage (PO:0025602) during which the pollen (PO:0025281) develops.

label.value: C callose wall formation in pollen mother cells stage

value.value: Stage during which diploid pollen mother cells become separated from each other and from tapetum by a callose wall.

label.value: D pollen mother cell meiosis stage

value.value: Stage during which pollen mother cells undergo meiosis to form tetrads of microspores.
Stage of microgametophyte development during which the callose wall between the tetrads breaks down and haploid microspores are released and lie freely in locules.
An initial stage during which the archesporial cells divide to give rise to primary parietal and sporogenous cells.
Stage of microgametophyte development during which the microspores round up and small vacuoles appear in their cytoplasm. The microspore walls thicken due to the formation of the exine.
Stage of microgametophyte development during which a large vacuole is formed in each microspore causing a rapid increase in size and a displacement of the nucleus to one side.

Stage of microgametophyte development during which the asymmetric, first mitotic division of the microspores occurs producing a large vegetative cell and small generative cell, located near pollen wall.
A pollen development stage (PO:0001007) during which the generative cell (PO:0020097) undergoes mitotic division to form two male gametes, the pollen sperm cells (PO:0025121).

definition.value: In taxa with mature two-celled pollen (PO:0025281), the second mitotic division takes place after pollen germination (GO:0009846), in the germinating pollen tube cell (PO:0025195). Note: This term overlaps with the GO BP term: generative cell mitosis (GO:0055047): The process in which the generative cell divides by mitosis to form two haploid cells. These will subsequently differentiate into sperm cells.

value.value: Stage of microgametophyte development during which the pollen reaches mature stage and desiccates.

definition.value: Mature pollen stages is reached at three-celled pollen in some angiosperms (maize, rice and Arabidopsis), while in others, the maturepollen has two haploid cells (tobacco, snapdragon).

value.value: The final stage in the life cycle of the male gametophyte. Upon rehydration, mature pollen grain forms a tubular outgrowth, the pollen tube, which carries the male gametes.

label.value: B formation of primary parietal and sporogenous cells stage

value.value: Stage during which the primary parietal and primary sporogenous layers are derived from archesporial cells.
A vascular leaf initiation stage (PO:0001051) during which a vascular leaf primordium (PO:0000017) forms in the peripheral zone (PO:0000225) of the vegetative shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148).

definition.value: The vascular leaf primordium (PO:0000017) develops from the vascular leaf anlagen (PO:0025431).

value.value: Stage of leaf development when a hood-shaped primordium is formed, partially enclosing P1 and SAM, as in Poaceae.
A vascular leaf expansion stage (PO:0001052) when conical P3 leaf completely encloses SAM, and the ligule (PO:0020105) primordium is visible.

label.value: rapid elongation of vascular leaf lamina stage

value.value: A vascular leaf expansion stage (PO:0001052) during which a rapid elongation of the leaf lamina (PO:0020039) occurs.

label.value: rapid elongation of leaf sheath stage

value.value: A vascular leaf expansion stage (PO:0001052) during which a rapid elongation of the leaf sheath (PO:0020104) occurs.

label.value: C four anther lobes formed stage

value.value: Stage during which the four-lobed anther pattern with two developing stomium regions (notch) are formed.
Stage during which the four clearly defined locules are established. All anther cell types present and microspore mother cells appear.
Stage immediately following meiosis, during which the tetrads of microspores are still hold together, enclosed by the callose wall.
The stage at which a root is elongating.

definition.value: In some plant species this stage is subdivided into distal and proximal elongating zones.

label.value: E anther wall tapetum degeneration initiated stage

value.value: An anther development stage (PO:0001004) during which degeneration of the anther wall tapetum (PO:0009071) is initiated, as the deposition on the surface of the microspore (PO:0020048) primexine proceeds.

definition.value: Microspores within single locule are at unicellular stage.

value.value: Stage during which anther becomes bilocular, after degeneration and breakage of septum below stomium.
Stage during which the dehiscence of anthers occurs. Anther breaks along stomium and pollen is released.
Stage during which the senescence of anther and stamen occurs. Shrinkage of cells and anther structure takes place.
A seed development stage (PO:0001170) during which the mature seed reaches a low moisture content.

label.value: chalazal and micropylar domain establishment stage

value.value: The initial stage of endosperm development during which the chalazal and micropilar domains are established.

label.value: functional specialization of the endosperm stage

value.value: Stage of endosperm development during which the functional specialization of the maturing endosperm occurs.
Stage of calyx development defined by differentiation and expansion of sepal.
Stage of calyx development when sepal is fully expanded.
A phyllome development stage (PO:0025579) that has as a primary participant a lemma (PO:0009037).
A phyllome development stage (PO:0025579) that has as a primary participant a palea (PO:0009038).
A phyllome development stage (PO:0025579) that has as a primary participant a lodicule (PO:0009036).
A phyllome development stage (PO:0025579) during which the development of vascular leaves (PO:0009025) and non-vascular leaves (PO:0025075) occurs.

A vascular leaf development stage (PO:0025570) which begins with the onset of the vascular leaf anlagen formation stage (PO:0001003) and ends with the termination of the vascular leaf primordium polarity determination stage (PO:0001052).

definition.value: Localized cell divisions in the peripheral zone (PO:0000225) transition from anticlinal to periclinal divisions.

value.value: A vascular leaf development stage (PO:0025570) during which vascular leaf size increases primarily through cell expansion.

definition.value: During this stage leaf shaping (GO:0010358) occurs which is defined as the developmental process that pertains to the organization of a leaf in three-dimensional space once the structure has initially formed.

value.value: A vascular leaf development stage (PO:0025570) that begins when the vascular leaf (PO:0009025) is fully expanded and ends with the onset of the vascular leaf senescence stage (PO:0001054).
A vascular leaf development stage (PO:0025570) that begins with the formation of a abscission zone at the base of a vascular leaf (PO:0009025) and ends with leaf separation and death.
Stage of lemma development that begins when the lemma primordia arise.

definition.value: The lemma primordium forms in 1/2 alternate phylotaxy in rice spikelet.

value.value: Stage of lemma development defined by differentiation and expansion of lemma.
